Q. Do you remember the box delivered to you at Dickinson's? - A. Yes; I know the box; I tied it to the back of the cart; it was tied fast; I accompanied the cart to the Hampshire Hog, at Hammersmith; there I left the cart, and met it about half an hour after;
Thomas Dalley
was with it.

GEORGE HODDY sworn. - I keep the Queen's Head;
John Carter
was my servant; he is since dead; I never saw Climer before that morning to my knowledge.
